summary: I still can’t get over people in the mcu and also irl who don’t like iron man complaining that he’s ‘just a man in a suit’...
body: I still can’t get over people in the mcu and also irl who don’t like iron man complaining that he’s ‘just a man in a suit’ because like???? nat??? hawkeye??? sam??? show me their powers??? they’re just well trained fighters??? honestly since they don’t have protective suits they’re more of a liability than tony is??? not to mention like. no one ever says that about rhodey??? plus ant-man and wasp are also just normal people in suits??? captain america’s superpower is just bringing his fists to a gun fight and looking like adonis. bucky literally only has the metal arm and good training. none of the guardians had any powers before mantis joined. stephan strange had no idea what the fuck was going on for the entirety of his movie and they still made him the minister of magic for some reason. peter parker could bench press a few elephants and yet for some reason he couldn’t pull the gauntlet off thanos’s hand. what I’m trying to say is every single character is a fucking trainwreck in their own right and idk why y’all wanna focus so much on iron man not having any powers when so far he’s been doing a pretty good job without them lmao
